Date: Tue 20 Nov 2001
From: Paul Newman <Paul.Newman@HCAHealthcare.com> [edited

The Interpretation of Scab Formation
------------------------------------
Many of these e-mails have indicated that the formation of a scab upon
re-vaccination equates to prior susceptibility; while, the lack of same
equates to immunity. What is the status of someone who was vaccinated
multiple times and NEVER developed a scab or scar? Some of the literature
indicates a natural immunity and some indicates no immunity.
--
P. Kenneth Newman, RN, B.S., COHN-S
Occupational Health
<Paul.Newman@HCAHealthcare.com>
[Being a person in the latter category, I would welcome a prediction. -
Mod.CP
